      <p>Proper earthing is one of the most critical aspects of electrical safety, yet it is routinely absent or inadequate in Pakistani homes built before the 1990s, and often even in more recent constructions. Without proper earthing, any fault current from a faulty appliance has nowhere to go except through the person touching it.</p>
